title: What makes a Bruegel a Bruegel (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
What makes a Bruegel a Bruegel?
Metropolitan Museum of Art & Viking | 1993 | English | 52 pages | PDF | 7.98 MB


Explores such art topics as style, composition, color, and subject matter as they relate to twelve works by Bruegel. From the former Vice Director for Education at the world renowned Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York City comes an art appreciation series unlike any other. In a handsomely deisgned, innovative format, this unique series explores the qualities that make one artist's work different from another. Full-color reproductions
